node.text:
Watching Katie’s dramatic hometowns calls for a few bottles of @spadeandsparrows 🍷 #mostdramaticseasonever 

Congrats to our Trivia winners @cashandjune_thecatahoulas @armnalegranch.corgis @apupcalledmika @mochi.the.yorkiee @myislandheelers - you’ve each won a bottle of @spadeandsparrows wine!

Cheers to every who watched and played along 🐶🥂Stay tuned for what’s bound to be the most dramatic episode yet 🌹 #thebachelorette

node.text:
Every dog deserves a great portrait. But it can be tricky when they refuse to sit still! After all, how are you supposed to take good photos when your pup is running around like a maniac?! Here are some tips from a professional pet photographer, @takebetterphotosofyourdog, on how to take photos of dogs who won’t sit still. 

📸 Link in bio to read our blog article!

node.title: How To Take Photos of Dogs Who Won’t Sit Still

node.text:
We’re launching a Tuesday TIP OF THE WEEK series to help answer some commonly asked questions from our community! Today we’re kicking off with our friend @takebetterphotosofyourdog 📸 

Every dog deserves a great portrait. But it’s not always possible to hire a professional photographer, and most people don’t own a DSLR or mirrorless camera. Luckily, cell phones come with pretty good built-in cameras these days!

Watch this video for a list of tips that'll help you be a better photographer - with your cell phone! Be sure to ready our blog (LINK IN BIO) or download the guide on www.dogphototips.com 

We’ll focus one week a month on how to take better photos of your dog, so leave your questions in the comments and tune back in next month for the answers! 

Check out more tips from Take Better Photos of Your Dog: @takebetterphotosofyourdog
Cover photo: @marshygsp 

#dogphotography #takebetterphotosofyourdog #photographytips #tuesdaytip #dogsofinstagram #tipoftheweek #phototips #dogphotos #dogphotoshoot

node.title: How To Take Better Photos of Your Dog With Your Phone

node.text:
Did you know 17.6 billion pounds of plastic are dumped into the oceans each year? That’s like 57,000 blue whales! Join our #EarthsBestFriend Cleanup Challenge in partnership with @projectblusocial to help make life better for pets, people, and the planet!

JOIN THE MOVEMENT AND EVERYONE WINS! We’re partnering with @projectblusocial and other sustainable brands around the world such as @pelacase,@barxbypet, @theouai, @farmbrandinspires, @mudjeans, @goldilocksgoods , @shamelesspets, @brooklyngrooming, and @4Earthapp to bring awareness to the best practices for reducing waste. 

Submit a photo of you and your pet cleaning up your community for the chance to win over $1,500 worth of eco-friendly products that will make you feel as good as you look. PLUS, every entry gets a tree planted through @onetreeplanted. Contest open from April 22-May 22. 

🌏 LINK IN BIO TO SUBMIT 🌍

Huge shoutout to our amazing @dogsofinstagram community for helping clean up and protect our planet! In no particular order:

@kaleiahskyy @apupcalledmika @dognamedbrewski @petitepokey @chewy_bernedoodle @darrelthedoge @dextersvida @puppies.n.pinot @frankandgary @gerti.b_ @kip.and.his.tongue @leo.eat.sleep.retrieve @leothemountainboy @lucasandperla_theiggies @luna_the_yorkiepoo @pepe_the_golden @rigby.corgi @sunnysbestlife @thismudderfluffer @whenashmetbowser @amyjaym 

🎥 edits: @tyleroo 

#earthsbestfriend #earthday #earthdaycleanupchallenge #gogreen #sustainability #ecofriendly #ecofriendlypetproducts #sustainablepetproducts #ecofriendlybeautyproducts #sustainablebeautyproducts #reduceplastic #carbonneutral #carbonpositive #positivechange #projectblu #dogsofinstagram

This giveaway is hosted by @DogsOfInstagram and ProjectBlu, in partnership with OUAI, Pela, Barxby, Farm Brand, Mud Jeans, Shameless Pets, Brooklyn Grooming, Goldilocks Goods, and 4Earth. Privacy Policy can be found on Sweepstakes landing page. This Giveaway is not sponsored, endorsed or administered by, or associated with Instagram. Giveaway will start April 22 (12:00am PST) and end May 22nd (11:59pm PST). Must be 18+. Prizes limited to U.S. residents. Featured photos open internationally.

node.text:
By now, you've probably heard how CBD can be beneficial for both humans and pets alike. For those new to the conversation, CBD is a derived from hemp or cannabis and does not contain THC, which is the substance that produces a high for its users. 

In 2018, a Cornell study reported 80% of osteoarthritis dogs who used CBD showed “significant improvement in pain levels and quality of life”. 

In a world where too many pets are homeless, abandoned, or returned, CBD seems to offer a ray of hope. The potential to steady a dog’s nerves long enough to charm a family, relieve a joint pain, aid in separation anxiety, or help behave when meeting new people could make all the difference in a pet’s life. Incorporating CBD into a consistent routine is one practice that can support this transition and pave the way for calm, happy families. 

Link in bio to read more about how CBD can help animals or donate a CBD product to a shelter pet through @welovecuddly! 

#dogsofinstagram #cbdforpets #cbdhealth #theanxiouspet #releasethepeace #relaxandroll @theanxiouspet

node.title: Free to Be CBD: How Hemp Products Can Help Rescue Animals

node.text:
How ‘bout that happy dance #dinnertime

Does food make you dance happy? 🕺🏽

🎥: @thotmania69 on Tiktok 

[visual description: a Dachshund spins around in circles with excitement when it’s dinner time.]

#dogsofdinnertime #dinnertimedogs #happydance #happydancedogs #dogsofinstagram #dachshundsofig

Meet Mojo, our Rescue Giveback Pup of the Month! Mojo is a one-year-old rescue Pit Bull in Simi Valley, CA, who was struck by a car in a hit and run. Mojo's leg was broken in two places, her hip was dislocated, and her ACL on her knee was torn on another leg.  We’re helping raise the $2,000 necessary for Mojo’s leg surgery through @waggleforpets. Join us at the link in our bio. ❤️‍🩹

"We were heartbroken when we heard about her," says Mark R., the founder of Southern California Pit Bull Rescue (@socalpitbullrescue). His nonprofit organization raced to Mojo's rescue after the shelter made a post saying the dog's injuries were too severe for them to handle. "My rescue fixes dogs like this. This is what we do. No dog is too challenging for us. We are the voice for the voiceless," he says. 

Will you join us in making sure Mojo gets the care and assistance she deserves? Link in bio to donate! 

Mark wants to thank anyone who can give to Mojo's campaign; paying off her medical bills helps the rescue save more pups in the future just like her, "We depend on people who are generous and tenderhearted to be able to help the animals who need us."

With your donations, we will have the ability to turn this tragedy into a happy outcome.
Once Mojo has fully recovered from surgeries, she will be available for adoption where she hopes to unite with his forever family. 💞

@waggleforpets is a wonderful organization that carefully evaluates each campaign and administers the funds directly to the vet working with rescue. Any funds raised in excess of the goal get put towards other pets needing help on the website. Donate at the link in our bio!

#rescuedogsofinstagram #rescuedogsinnerd #waggle #supportrescuedogs #dogsinneed #dogsofshelters #giveback #dogsinneed #voiceforthevoiceless
